Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{}, sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Trim the @carrots{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly
1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Pop the carrot batons onto a large baking tray.
Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread
out in a single layer.

Add the @British honey mustard sausages{8} to the same tray.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages. TIP: Use
> two baking trays if necessary.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until the sausages are cooked through,
~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything roasts, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated)
(or use a #garlic press{}).

When there are about 10 mins left of roasting time left, heat a drizzle of
@oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the garlic. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}. Add in the
@chicken stock paste{10%grams} and @water{75%ml}, bring to the boil until
reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once reduced, stir in the @creme fraiche{75%grams} and @wholegrain mustard{17%grams}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder). Bring back to the boil, reduce the
heat and simmer until everything's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When the carrots and sausages have 5 mins of cooking time remaining, carefully
drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp}, toss to coat, then return to the oven.

When everything's ready, share the sausages between your plates.

Serve the herby chips and honey roasted carrots alongside.

Finish by spooning over your creamy mustard sauce. Enjoy!